---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import StoreButtons from '../components/StoreButtons.astro';

const breadcrumbs = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@type': 'BreadcrumbList',
  itemListElement: [
    { '@type': 'ListItem', position: 1, name: 'Home', item: 'https://myglu.health/' },
    { '@type': 'ListItem', position: 2, name: 'About', item: 'https://myglu.health/about' },
  ],
};
---

<Layout
  title="About Glu — Tracking Built for GLP-1 Treatment"
  description="Why we built Glu: a calm, focused tracker for life on GLP-1 medications — shots, doses, side effects, and progress in one place, made by the independent studio Layline."
  canonicalPath="/about"
  structuredData={breadcrumbs}
>
  <div class="min-h-screen bg-slate-50 text-slate-900">
    <header class="sticky top-0 z-50 border-b border-slate-100 bg-white/80 backdrop-blur-xl">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-screen-md px-6 py-6 sm:px-8">
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-3">
          <img src="/app_icon.png" alt="Glu" class="h-8 w-8 rounded-xl shadow-sm" width="32" height="32" />
          <span class="font-sora text-lg font-semibold tracking-tight text-slate-900">Glu</span>
        </a>
      </div>
    </header>

    <section class="mx-auto w-full max-w-screen-md px-6 pb-20 pt-16 sm:px-8 sm:pt-20">
      <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-slate-500">About</p>
      <h1 class="mt-3 font-sora text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-slate-900 sm:text-4xl">
        Tracking built for GLP-1 treatment
      </h1>

      <div class="mt-8 flex flex-col gap-6 font-dm-sans text-base leading-relaxed text-slate-700">
        <p>
          Glu exists because GLP-1 treatment generates a surprising amount to keep track of — a weekly
          shot on the right day, an injection site to rotate, side effects that come and go, doses that
          step up every few weeks, and weight that moves slowly enough to be easy to misread. Most apps
          were never built for that rhythm, so the tracking ends up scattered across notes, memory, and
          the back of a prescription box.
        </p>
        <p>
          We built one place for all of it. Glu keeps your shot day, dose history, injection sites, side
          effects, weight trends, meals and protein, and daily habits together — so the patterns that
          actually matter become visible. When your prescriber asks how it's been going, you arrive with
          a clear record instead of a best guess, and titration decisions get made on your data rather
          than your memory.
        </p>
        <p>
          It's made for people on semaglutide or tirzepatide — Wegovy, Ozempic, Zepbound, Mounjaro, or a
          compounded regimen — who want to understand their own treatment. The design goal is the lowest
          possible friction: a few taps on shot day, trends you can read at a glance, and nothing you
          have to fight to log. The best tracker is the one you'll actually keep using.
        </p>
        <p>
          Glu is a tracking and educational tool, not a medical device. It doesn't provide medical
          advice, diagnosis, or treatment — your prescriber knows your history, and important decisions
          belong with them.
        </p>
        <p>
          Glu is made by <a href="https://layline.ventures" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-slate-900 underline decoration-slate-300 underline-offset-4 transition-colors hover:decoration-slate-900">Layline</a>,
          a small independent studio (operated by Layline Ventures Tecnologia da Informação LTDA).
          Questions, feedback, or bug reports? Write to
          <a href="mailto:support@myglu.health" class="text-slate-900 underline decoration-slate-300 underline-offset-4 transition-colors hover:decoration-slate-900">support@myglu.health</a>
          or visit the <a href="/support" class="text-slate-900 underline decoration-slate-300 underline-offset-4 transition-colors hover:decoration-slate-900">support page</a>.
          You can also review our
          <a href="/privacy" class="text-slate-900 underline decoration-slate-300 underline-offset-4 transition-colors hover:decoration-slate-900">Privacy Policy</a>
          and <a href="/terms" class="text-slate-900 underline decoration-slate-300 underline-offset-4 transition-colors hover:decoration-slate-900">Terms of Service</a>.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-12">
        <StoreButtons />
      </div>
    </section>

    <Footer />
  </div>
</Layout>
